  <description><![CDATA[<p><a name="Top"></a></p>
<p> </p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a data-udi="umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912" href="/{localLink:umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912}#Highlights" title="Rome &amp; Sorrento" data-anchor="#Highlights">Highlights</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912" href="/{localLink:umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912}#Itinerary" title="Rome &amp; Sorrento" data-anchor="#Itinerary">Itinerary</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912" href="/{localLink:umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912}#Includes" title="Rome &amp; Sorrento" data-anchor="#Includes">Your holiday includes</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912" href="/{localLink:umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912}#Includes" title="Rome &amp; Sorrento" data-anchor="#Includes">Hotels</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912" href="/{localLink:umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912}#Dates" title="Rome &amp; Sorrento" data-anchor="#Dates">Departure dates</a></h2>
<p> </p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Highlights"></a>Highlights</h3>
<ul>
<li>Combine the sights and history of Rome with the popular Amalfi Coast</li>
<li>Explore the Colosseum, Vatican and Spanish Steps in Rome</li>
<li>This itinerary takes you to two of Italy's most popular destinations making it perfect for first-time visitors<br /><br /></li>
</ul>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Itinerary"></a>Itinerary</h3>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Rome</strong></p>
<p>Fly into <a data-udi="umb://document/57bc5f34b7074843b7f19f3fc6cb7ac4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/57bc5f34b7074843b7f19f3fc6cb7ac4}" title="Rome">Rome</a> and take a private transfer to your centrally located hotel. Unpack and head out for a walk around the city to get your bearings.</p>
<p><strong>Days 2-3: Rome</strong></p>
<p>There's ancient sights around every corner of <a data-udi="umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904}" title="Italy">Italy's</a> capital. Start with the Colosseum and Roman Forum - an expert guide on a pre-booked excursion will bring them to life as you walk around and see the ruins. It's well worth saving half a day to visit the Vatican where you can admire Michelangelo’s artwork in the Sistine Chapel and visit the impressive museums.</p>
<p>We love heading for the piazze when we're in Rome. Grab a couple of scoops of gelato and sit in front of the Trevi Fountain or find a chair in a café in Piazza Navona for some lunch and people watching.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Rome to Amalfi Coast</strong></p>
<p>Today you'll be leaving Rome and heading to the Amalfi Coast. A transfer will take you to Rome's station where you'll begin the high-speed journey to Naples. You'll be in Campania's capital in less than an hour and a half and a private transfer will take you onto your chosen coastal town where you'll arrive in time for dinner. </p>
<p><strong>Days 5-10: Amalfi Coast</strong></p>
<p>All of our Amalfi Coast resorts are great bases for hopping from place to place along the coast<a data-udi="umb://document/7e6d84fc86844d12b8c73851f2035fb1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7e6d84fc86844d12b8c73851f2035fb1}" title="Neapolitan Riviera"></a>. Book a few excursions to get the most out of your stay. The Amalfi Drive is a must-do. A coach will take you along the coastal road to visit towns like Positano and Ravello. Grab a seat on the right hand side of the bus on your way for the best views.</p>
<p>You must leave some time to explore Pompeii too. It's a fascinating place to see and most excursions will take you up Mount Vesuvius afterwards where you'll get panoramic views across the Bay of Naples.</p>
<p><strong>Day 11: Amalfi Coast to UK</strong></p>
<p>Say goodbye to The Amalfi Coast with a final coffee or limoncello in a local cafe before taking a private transfer to Naples airport for your flight home.<br /><br /></p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Includes"></a>Your holiday includes</h3>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from the UK</li>
<li>Private transfer from Rome airport to your hotel and from your hotel to the station</li>
<li>Train travel from Rome to Naples</li>
<li>Private transfer from Naples station to your hotel on the Amalfi Coast and to Naples airport</li>
<li>10 nights accommodation<br /><br /></li>
</ul>
<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Excursions<br /><br /></li>
</ul>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Hotels"></a>Hotels</h3>
<p>Choose from any of our hotels in <a data-udi="umb://document/57bc5f34b7074843b7f19f3fc6cb7ac4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/57bc5f34b7074843b7f19f3fc6cb7ac4}" title="Rome">Rome</a> or the Amalfi Coast. You can change the durations to create your perfect holiday. Give us a call to discuss your options.<br /><br /></p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Dates"></a>Departure dates</h3>
<p>Flexible daily departures from May to October.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a data-udi="umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912" href="/{localLink:umb://document/53a09958cf634d47abf56c4efd5c7912}#Top" title="Rome &amp; Sorrento" data-anchor="#Top">[Back to top]</a></p>]]></description>
